summary: I just realized that all of the stark reunions revolve around Sansa. Sansa and Jon, then Sansa and Bran, and then Sansa and...
question: I just realized that all of the stark reunions revolve around Sansa. Sansa and Jon, then Sansa and Bran, and then Sansa and Arya. Do you think there's any significance to everyone reuniting with Sansa first?
answer:
In a way.

I’ve always thought that Sansa thinking of herself as the blood of Winterfell in the books was very telling. Her ancestral home is where she drew strength from in her times of greatest need. And in s6, she and Jon were the ones to fight for it and restore it, along with the North. All of the Stark children reuniting with Sansa represents them coming home, touching base with their roots again. I think out of all of them, Sansa will be the one to ensure their survival. She represents House Stark’s future.

title: Game of Thrones Rewatch 2.05
body:
1. Yeah, Stannos is foul for doing Renly like that. But you know, all’s fair…

2. Man, Brienne is a badass with a sword.

3. “And I say father raised you to have too much respect for money.”

“Yes, I know how concerned you are for her safety.” “So happens that I am. Myrcella is a sweet, innocent girl and I don’t blame her at all for you.”

“May I ask specifically what the king has in mind?” “You may specifically or you may ask vaguely, the answer will be the same.”

I love Tyrion and Cersei together, honestly.

4. “Swear to me on what?” “On my life!” “But I don’t care about your life.” Hahaha.

5. “We’ve underestimated the Stark boy for too long. He has a good mind for warfare, his men worship him and as long as he keeps winning battles, they’ll keep believing he’s King in the North. We keep waiting for him to fail, he’s not going to fail. Not without our help.”

6. “If your name wasn’t Lannister you’d be cleaning pots in the kitchen.” So petty.

7. “And what do they say of Robb Stark in the North?” “They call him the young wolf.” “And?” “They say he rides into battle on the back of a giant direwolf. They say he can turn into a wolf himself when he wants. They say he can’t be killed.” “And do you believe them?” “No, my Lord. Anyone can be killed.” 1) I love that Arya just came up with that on the spot 2) I love that there’s a sense of Northern and sibling pride in her description 3)  I like how after she says “Anyone can be killed” Tywin regards her and you see a flicker of him being impressed with her. 4) I love her scenes with Tywin. I feel like a lot of Maisie’s best acting comes out with certain scene partners.

8. I won’t lie, I forgot about Jon.

9. “Beautiful isn’t it? Gilly would love it here!” Oh Sam, you met her for like three days. I love it.

10. “Before I die, please, stop talking.” An entire mood.

11. I very much prefer post-dead Jon.

12. I feel like there has to be a better way to store wild fire.

13. Legit, Daenerys doesn’t want to be a khaleesi, she just wants to collect titles but that’s none of my business.

14. There’s an ethereal quality to Osha’s voice.

15. D’aww Sam is such a good friend.

16.“Do not speak to me like I’m a child.” Then stop acting like one.

17. “You have a gentle heart.” Mmmmm not really.

18. That time when Arya went through her sexual awakening looking at Gendry. I get it.

19. JUST GET MARRIED.
